# SDD Studio

SDD Studio targets **web, mobile-native, and hybrid** client applications. It is not designed for terminal-only or CLI-primary products.

## Official cycle

```text
Idea → Brief → Specification → Planning → Implementation → Code
```

Each stage answers a different question.

## Document map

| Location | Question |
| -------- | -------- |
| `.workspace/brief/manifest.yaml` | Which semver version of each brief lane is active or in draft? |
| `.workspace/brief/business/<semver>/product-principles.md` | What conceptual principles is the product built on? |
| `.workspace/brief/business/<semver>/product-guide.md` | How does the product work for a user? |
| `.workspace/brief/technical/<semver>/engineering-principles.md` | What engineering principles guide the product? |
| `.workspace/brief/technical/engineering-decisions.md` | What architectural decisions have been made? |
| `.workspace/brief/technical/engineering-conventions.md` | What development conventions apply? |
| `.workspace/brief/technical/engineering-frontend-patterns.md` | How should frontend features behave (data flow, filters, loading, notifications)? |
| `.workspace/brief/technical/engineering-backend-patterns.md` | How should APIs respond (envelopes, errors, pagination metadata)? |
| `.workspace/brief/technical/engineering-contribution-patterns.md` | How does the team branch, commit, promote environments, and merge PRs? |
| `.workspace/brief/technical/engineering-stack.md` | What technologies do we use? |
